race.comment: RUBINSKY (7) opened this prep with a couple of close seconds then stepped out to 1250m at Taree last start and didn't quite finish it off, narrowly missing the placings. Suited coming back in trip and with any luck from the wide gate can open her account. VIDIA (11) returns from a 170-day spell. Raced twice in the maiden campaign and wasn't far away on either occasion. Has trialled three times since mid-January so she should be forward enough to run a big race. RIVER JORDAN (3) is a Street Boss gelding on debut for the Dilmi stable. Easily took out a Wyong trial recently so he looks to have his share of talent. BRITISH NAVY (16) was poor at Goulburn last start but might improve with blinkers going on for the first time. DAWN RIDER (1) is a first starter from the Maher stable. Trials have been average but the early betting suggests he has a bit more to offer.
